$interpreted: Tica: Are you guys trying to infect her?
Tica: I will NOT let you guys disturb her time with Karl!
Tica: Eh? Are you going to help me too?
Tica: Very well. Then let's go kick butt together!
Tica: Muhahaha~ Now you know how powerful I am!
Tica: Done and~ DONE!!!
Tica: Rest assured, I've taken care of them all. You're no longer in harm's way.
Tica: No need to thank me. Your devotion to your little master really touched me...
Tica: That's why I decided to offer my help!
Tica: ...And a small part of it is also because I feel bad since I was the one who injured you. I won't be so reckless in the future. I'm sorry...
Tica: Gotta go. Need to report these things to headmaster ASAP.
Tica: Be careful in the future. If you see monsters, remember to hide!
Tica: Buh-bye~!
Uzziah: While she was at Workshop VI, if she realized that the singing was not the main reason for the rampaging marionettes...
Uzziah: ...this fiasco would have ended a long time ago.
Uzziah: Besides, the marionettes started attacking people due to a rune command error caused by the monsters' attack.
Uzziah: Yet she used the word "infect", a term that only applies to creatures. It's like she's viewing the marionettes as an organic life form.
Uzziah: It's just like the people hundreds of year ago. The marionettes are just meaninglessly carrying out rune commands.
Uzziah: Yet they believed these actions to be a showcase of emotion. Why?
Uzziah: When your master needed help, the humans at the time didn't even bother to bat an eye.
Uzziah: However, after he died, they projected emotion onto you. Thus creating a cultural practice that lasted several hundred years...
Uzziah: Is this how finite beings' search for redemption in the midst of reincarnation?
Patrolling Soldier: Eh, you? That was fast; thought you're going to be in there a lot longer.
Patrolling Archer: She definitely got scared inside. That's why she got out so quickly. She is just a little girl after all.
Tica: Hehe, I experienced a lot of interesting things in there!
Tica: However, I have to apologize. I was reckless before, I'm sorry. Are you guys alright?
Patrolling Soldier: Umm, it's ok. As long as you're safe, we don't mind. No need for you to be so modest.
Patrolling Archer: Yeah, we're elite border guards! Attacks from a kid like you won't even leave a scratch!
Tica: How reliable! Then if those freaky marionettes come out, I'll trust you guys to take care of them.
Patrolling Archer: ...F-Freaky marionettes?
Patrolling Soldier: Wait, why would they even come out!?
Tica: They like to creep up behind you out of nowhere. So you guys better watch your back, literally, at night...
Patrolling Archer: ...B-Behind us!?
Tica: Yep. Ah, but you don't need to be scared of the marionettes with dead people's souls attached to them. Those won't come out.
Patrolling Archer: ... D-Dead people!?
Patrolling Soldier: Just what in god's name did you witness in there!?
Tica: That's about it. You guys are now in charge of dealing with them. I've got missions to complete. See ya~
Patrolling Soldier: ...A-Are there really ghosts inside!?
Patrolling Archer: Hey, don't run so fast! Can you please explain what you said more clearly!? W-We need that information!
